<P>
   KOSOVO-PILOTS (Washington) _ Peering down at the ground from
15,000 feet or higher, NATO pilots like those who apparently
attacked civilians in Kosovo by mistake rely on a combination of
technology and their own eyesight to identify what they are seeing.
By Richard W. Stevenson.
