</P>
<P>
   AIRLINE-REPORT (Washington) _ The major airlines are getting
worse at many of the parts of their job that passengers care about
the most: on-time performance, lost baggage, and being treated
decently on the trip. The findings come from the National Airline
Quality Rating, produced by business professors at the University
of Nebraska and Wichita State University based on statistics
reported to the government. By Matthew L. Wald.
</P>
<P>
   BRADLEY-PROFILE (Washington) _ A political profile of Bill
Bradley, the New Jersey Democrat; the first in series of occasional
profiles of presidential contenders. By Richard L. Berke.
</P>
<P>
   WIS-WELFARE (Milwaukee) _ Michelle Crawford's odyssey _ from
desperation to distinction, from welfare to work _ is indeed a
powerful, inspiring story. It is also an incomplete one, at least
in its official telling. After years of severe anxiety and
depression, Ms. Crawford, 39, is indeed off welfare and on the job
at a plastics factory outside Milwaukee. Her diligent record
recently earned her a raise, to $8.20 an hour. But behind the
scenes, her accomplishments have also placed new burdens on a life
that is much more difficult than her admirers realize and less
steady than the governor may hope. By Jason DeParle.
</P>
