<P>
   COMPAQ (Undated) _ As Compaq Computer Corp. begins its search
for a new chief executive, it is clear that the incoming leader's
first challenge will be to chart a course from the brick-and-mortar
retailers that have been the company's life blood to the
direct-sales model that is increasingly defining the industry's
future. By Lawrence M. Fisher.
</P>
<P>
   ASIA-MARKETPLACE (Hong Kong) _ Stock markets from South Korea to
Singapore soared Monday, extending a rally that many analysts here
say is proof that foreign investors are returning in large numbers
to the recession-ravaged economies of Asia. By Mark Landler.
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ Oprah Winfrey has her reading club,
but she is not alone among celebrities trying to persuade more
Americans to pick up a book. By Dana Canedy.
</P>
