   &UR; CULTURE (Moved in ``e'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MET-GREEK-CORRIDOR (New York) _ The most spectacular space to be
opened in New York City since the renovation of Grand Central
Station is unveiled, and like Grand Central it is also a
refurbished landmark: the 140-foot-long Neoclassical barrel-vaulted
corridor to the south of the main lobby, or Great Hall, in the
Metropolitan Museum of Art. By Michael Kimmelman.
</P>
