<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ If real people weren't really being killed, the
eruption of Serb outrage at NATO's mistaken bombing of a caravan of
fleeing Kosovars could be amusing. Here is a government _ and
increasingly, sad to say, a population as well _ pretending for
world consumption to be distressed at NATO's accidental killing of
the very people Serbia itself is energetically and very, very
purposely brutalizing. (Tom Teepen is national correspondent for
Cox Newspapers.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ The great hockey player Wayne Gretzky was
retiring Sunday, and it was the second day of the professional
football draft. With both on TV, it was an opportunity to surf
between them. The contrast became remarkable. (Howard Kleinberg is
a columnist for Cox News Service.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
