<P>
   PageExpress, a new service from The New York Times Syndicate,
consists of paginated pages built with content from Cox Newspapers
and The New York Times News Service. The pages are easy to retrieve
from a web site. You can use them just as they are or customize any
or all of the elements _ text, fonts, photos and graphics _ to suit
your needs.
</P>
<P>
   For more information on these pages, or to view a sample, use
your web browser to visit http://nytsyn.com/pageexpress.
</P>
<P>
   For the password to download and use the pages, call Bob Farnell
at The New York Times Syndicate: 800-972-3550 or e-mail him at
farnellb &LR; nytimes.com.
</P>
<P>
   Unless otherwise noted, pages are available after 2 p.m. Tue.,
April 20.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FOCUS (Available by 2 p.m., Fri., April 23) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGE WILL INCLUDE ONE COLOR ILLUSTRATION, ONE GRAPHIC.
</P>
<P>
   NATO ANNIVERSARY: For four decades, NATO stood sentry at
Europe's eastern doorstep, poised to unleash massive tanks,
intercontinental bombers and, if need be, nuclear warheads to
thwart the military threat of the Soviet Union. Deterrence worked:
The Soviet Union collapsed. And yet, as the largest summit of world
leaders ever assembled gathers to mark NATO's 50th anniversary,
NATO is being tested by a symptom of its own success. (Will include
3-column color illustration and 2-column information graphic.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT (Available by 2 p.m., Thu., April 22) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGE WILL INCLUDE FOUR COLOR PHOTOS AND ONE COLOR ILLUSTRATION.
</P>
