   &UR; FOOD &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGE INCLUDES TWO COLOR PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTHERN PRIDE: ITALIAN CREAM CAKE: When Southerners celebrate
with a birthday party, holiday dinner, wedding reception or
graduation gathering, what is the cake of choice? Chances are, it's
Italian cream cake. Little is known about its origin _ except that
it isn't Italian, it contains no cream other than cheese and few
outside the South have ever heard of it. Yet this blond, moist,
three-layer cake is the pride of both home and commercial bakers,
from Texas to Georgia. (Includes one 4-column photo of original
cream cake and one 1-column photo of chocolate cream cake.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: CAKE RECIPES: Chocolate Italian Cream Cake, Original
Italian Cream Cake.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: CYBERSPICE: To explore the origins of the food we eat is
never to look at a salad bar quite the same way again. Tracing the
history of everyday foods _ those we may take for granted _ can
lead to something as lofty as the unfolding of civilization. Head
to food sites on the Web to learn of geography, history,
anthropology, science, culture, art and even religions of the
world.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: RECIPE: Rotelle With Asparagus and Mushroom Sauce
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHEELS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGE INCLUDES FOUR COLOR PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   CHEVY BLAZER: Finally, for 1999, Chevrolet has given its Blazer
an upscale option: the '99 TrailBlazer package. It includes
two-tone embossed leather seats, monochromatic paint and _ this is
significant _ a touring suspension that really smooths out the ride
of the 3,700-pound sport-utility. (Includes 3-column color photo of
