<P>
   SOUTHERN PRIDE: ITALIAN CREAM CAKE: When Southerners celebrate
with a birthday party, holiday dinner, wedding reception or
graduation gathering, what is the cake of choice? Chances are, it's
Italian cream cake. Little is known about its origin _ except that
it isn't Italian, it contains no cream other than cheese and few
outside the South have ever heard of it. Yet this blond, moist,
three-layer cake is the pride of both home and commercial bakers,
from Texas to Georgia. (Includes one 4-column photo of original
cream cake and one 1-column photo of chocolate cream cake.)
