<P>
   The New York Times plans three pages of stories, photos and
graphics on the continuing crisis in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-U.S. (Washington) _ Developments in Washington on Kosovo:
Albright, Cohen and Berger hold briefing. By Katharine Q. Seelye.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Brussels) _ Kosovo and the NATO summit as NATO
officials get ready to move to Washington for the weekend. By Craig
R. Whitney.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-MILITARY (Washington) _ Daily developments from the
Pentagon. By Eric Schmitt.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-FAMILY (Kukes, Albania) _ One family's story: When Ymer
Behrami crossed the border from Kosovo he had no idea he was
leaving one nightmare only to enter another. One where the
apartment he expected to be waiting for him in Albania would never
appear. Where getting food, even a piece of bread, would force him
to fight and claw like an animal. Where the intimidation and
humiliation he thought he had left behind would find him. By
Anthony DePalma.
</P>
<P>
   With photos.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-MACEDONIA (Skopje, Macedonia) _ More refugees are blocked
by Macedonians officials; U.N. officials say they're not getting
food, either. Macedonians say they will expand their camps. By
David Rohde.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-RUSSIA (Moscow) _ Kosovo developments: Folo on
yesterday's phone talk between Presidents Clinton and Yeltsin. By
Celestin eBohlen.
</P>
