<HEADLINE>
THE REPUBLICANS' ABORT FACE 
 A COLUMNIST WITH SOMETHING TO OFFEND EVERYONE 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SLATE, the premier online magazine of politics and culture, is
now available to your readers from The New York Times Syndicate.
</P>
<P>
   Today:
</P>
<P>
   1. THE REPUBLICANS' ABORT FACE by Michael Kinsley
</P>
<P>
   What is especially enjoyable about the Republican Party's agony
over abortion is that the leading Republican lights are almost
surely pro-choice in their hearts.
</P>
<P>
   1,300 words. Slugged: BC-KINSLEY-SLATE-NYTSF
</P>
<P>
   -------
</P>
<P>
   2. A COLUMNIST WITH SOMETHING TO OFFEND EVERYONE by A.O. Scott
</P>
<P>
   Newspaper commentary, a dying art, is nowadays dominated by
sententiousness, not satire. On the flat, windy landscape of the
nation's opinion pages, Pulitzer Prize-winner Maureen Dowd stands
out.
</P>
<P>
   1,800 words. Slugged: BC-SASSY-MAUREEN-DOWD-SLATE-NYTSF
