<SLUG> BC-GAYS-TRAVEL-$ADV24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    FACTS AND FIGURES ABOUT GAY TRAVELERS:
 &HT;    With CARIBBEAN-GAYS-$ADV24.
 &HT;    For Use (i) International and (t) Travel categories.
 &HT;    By SHELLEY EMLING 
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   THE MARKET:
</P>
<P>
   The American gay and lesbian community represents a $47.3
billion travel market, or about 10 percent of the U.S. travel
industry.
</P>
<P>
   American gay and lesbian travelers in the past 12 months . . .
</P>
<P>
   89 percent took vacations
</P>
<P>
   54 percent took 3 or more vacations
</P>
<P>
   15 percent took a cruise (national average is 2 percent)
</P>
<P>
   42 percent plan overseas/international trips in the next 12
months
</P>
<P>
   American gay and lesbian demographics . . .
</P>
<P>
   93 percent hold major credit cards
</P>
<P>
   82 percent hold a valid passport (national average is 18
percent)
</P>
<P>
   75 percent belong to frequent flyer programs
</P>
<P>
   54 percent budget $3,000 or more for a vacation
</P>
<P>
   Source: International Gay &AMP; Lesbian Travel Association.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
