   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   BKN-HEAT - Is Pat Riley going soft? He's given the Heat three
straight non-game days off now. (D'Angelo, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGE
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GATECH _ ATLANTA _ The NCAA has ruled in the case of Georgia
Tech coach George O'Leary, who admitted lending money to former
player C.J. Williams last year. The violation was deemed secondary,
but O'Leary faces the following penalties _ he can't coach in the
team's final scrimmage Saturday, can't recruit off-campus in May
and must coach from the press box in the season opener against
Navy. (Clemons, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) 12''
</P>
