balancing not just flavors and textures but workload _ mixing
labor-intensive appetizers with simpler recipes.
</P>
<P>
   ``Martha Stewart's Hors D'Oeuvres Handbook'' isn't for people
who stress out over cooking and entertaining; it will only add to
the pre-party jitters. But for those who know a bit about cooking
and can comfortably skip making pain de mie from scratch without
guilt, the book will let readers tap into Martha's brilliance.
</P>
<P>
   &LR; ``Martha Stewart's Hors D'Oeuvres Handbook,'' by Martha &LR; 
 &LR; Stewart (Clarkson N. Potter, 1999; 496 pages hardcover; $35). &LR;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
