<HEADLINE>
BEGINNER'S ESSENTIAL KITCHEN TOOLS  
 

</HEADLINE>
 CHRON  
 
 EDITORS NOTE: This is the second take of the San Francisco 
 Chronicle package introducing Marion Cunningham's new column, 
 ``Learning to Cook.'' The first take is slugged MARION. Please 
 also look for the column, slugged LEARN TO COOK. All pieces move 
 today.  The following kitchen equipment will serve your basic needs in
preparing, cooking and baking basic recipes:
<TEXT>
<P>
   2-cup saucepan with lid
</P>
<P>
   2-quart saucepan with lid
</P>
<P>
   6-quart saucepan with lid
</P>
<P>
   8-inch frying pan with lid
</P>
<P>
   10- or 12-inch saute pan with lid
</P>
<P>
   12x17-inch roasting pan
</P>
<P>
   Electric waffle iron
</P>
<P>
   8-cup ovenproof casserole
</P>
