<HEADLINE>
IT'S A VERY OLD BALKAN STORY
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Recently reading  &UR; Leo Tolstoy &LR; 's ``Anna Karenina,'' which was
published in 1878,  &UR; David Elliott  &LR; discovered some passages
relevant to today's headlines. After Anna Karenina committed
suicide (if you haven't read it, sorry to give that away), her
lover, Count Vronsky, volunteered to go to the Balkans to help the
Serbs, who were fighting the Turks:
</P>
<P>
   ``Nothing was talked of or written about just now but the
Serbian War ...'' wrote Tolstoy. It ``had become one of those
fashionable distractions which succeed one another in providing
society with an object and an occupation. ... A great many people
were taking up the subject from motives of self-interest and
self-advertisement. ... The newspapers published a great deal that
was superfluous and exaggerated, with the sole aim of attracting
attention and outcrying one another.
</P>
<P>
   ``The massacre of Slavs who were fellow Christians, and Slav
brethren, excited sympathy for the sufferers and indignation
against the oppressors. And the heroism of the Serbians and
Montenegrins, struggling for a great cause, begot in the whole
(Russian) people a longing to help their brothers not in word but
in deed.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DiCAPRIO LIVES SCENE FROM `TITANIC' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   There wasn't an iceberg in sight last Friday in Thailand, when a
boat in which  &UR; Leonardo DiCaprio  &LR; and  &UR; Tilda Swinton &LR;  were riding
while making ``The Beach'' was hit by waves and capsized.
</P>
<P>
   DiCaprio was in the water for five to 10 minutes, along with
tens of thousands of dollars worth of camera equipment. The actor
was said to have helped calm panicking crew members.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was a real gentleman,'' said  &UR; Santa Pestanij &LR; , Thai
coordinator for the movie. The moviemakers denied a report in the
British tabloid the Sun that the waters were shark-infested.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Beach'' has been a controversial project in Thailand,
where environmentalists have complained that the project has
damaged the ocean shoreline.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ALL TOGETHER, BOYS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``It's way beyond anything I imagined possible,''  &UR; George &LR; 
 &UR; Lucas &LR;  said in Wired magazine about the making of ``Star Wars:
Episode 1 _ The Phantom Menace.'' ``It's like the invention of
sound or color.''
</P>
<P>
   ``At the end of the day, you know something?'' star  &UR; Liam &LR; 
 &UR; Neeson  &LR; told Movieline magazine. ``It's just a movie.''
</P>
