trying to wipe out a whole population. A more apt comparison may be
with the United Nations' bloody ``police action'' in Korea, which
stopped communist expansion in the region. Nearly 50 years later
U.S. troops are still there, and North Korea is still a menace. By
MARIANNE MEANS. (Already filed.
