<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SHOOTINGS-CLERGY-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Clergy members seek to make sense of tragedy
 &HT;    By C. Patrick Cleary
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   LITTLETON, Colo. _ A Catholic church here Tuesday evening was
drawing people trying to make sense of the tragedy at Columbine
High School.
</P>
<P>
   Joe Dredon, a freshman at the school, stood next to the
baptismal font at Light of the World Catholic Church and
acknowledged to a friend that one of their best friends is dead.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just don't understand how they could take a life like
that,'' he said. ``He never even lived his life. Now he is gone. I
just .. `` Then he dissolved into grief and was wrapped in the arms
of neighbors and friends.
</P>
<P>
   The church, about three miles from the high school, sits on a
hill overlooking the valley where the tragedy occurred. Members of
the Littleton community continued to stream into the church Tuesday
evening, passing by groups of students, faculty and friends.
</P>
<P>
   ``The living water (of church baptism( is real important to me
right now,'' said counselor Julie McGuire, as she helped usher
people into the gymnasium-sized church. ``That is all I can think
of now. Tonight it is grieving. Tomorrow it is life.''
</P>
<P>
   Counselors and American Red Cross officials stood outside the
church, plotting strategy. Inside, Deb Nickerson, a church
volunteer, stood behind a table that had pamphlets on mental health
information and sign- up sheets for donations and people willing to
cook meals.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know who decided to do this,'' Nickerson said about
the meals. ``But people are just coming up and signing up without
question.''
</P>
<P>
   In the crowded area outside the church, drivers parked their
cars wherever they could and many people milled about, not really
knowing what to say or do.
</P>
<P>
   Cleary writes for the Daily Sentinel in Grand Junction, Colo.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
