   (NYT16) KUKES, Albania -- April 20, 1999 -- KOSOVO-REFUGEES-4,
4-20 -- Thousands of ethnic Albanian refugees from Kosovo line up
in a downtown square to receive some basic food supplies on
Tuesday. Thousands of refugees were trapped in a no man's land
inside Kosovo on Tuesday while refugee officials struggled to
handle the unpredictable flow of ethnic Albanians fleeing Kosovo.
(Edward Keating/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT15) NEW YORK -- April 20, 1999 -- RAGOUTS, 4-20 -- Vegetable
ragout in a celery cream sauce at Michael Jordan's steakhouse.
Spring vegetable ragouts are the dish of the moment, replacing
winter's sturdy roasted roots. The key ingredients, sweet young
things like spring garlic and baby onions, are in the market only a
month or two. Asparagus, baby carrots, fava beans and garden peas
sustain a longer stretch, but they, too, seem most suited to this
season. (Michael Rogol/New York Times Photo)
</P>
