<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-20 22:14 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6550 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CHILDREN-SLAIN-GRAPHI     04-20 0582
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CHILDREN-SLAIN-GRAPHIC-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DRAWINGS OF CHILDREN FOUND IN CREEK BED RELEASED 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
(Graphic containing mugs available) By POLLY ROSS HUGHES 
c. 1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   GEORGETOWN, Texas _ Desperate to identify the bodies of two
small children found dumped in a rural creek bed, authorities
released composite drawings Tuesday of a girl and boy who appear to
be related.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel that the good Lord will help us make identification of
those babies and hopefully today, tonight or tomorrow,'' said
Williamson County Sheriff Ed Richards. ``It's almost impossible to
establish motive without knowing who the victims are.''
</P>
<P>
   Richards said law enforcement officials believe the children
were murdered and are looking for any clues to solve the mystery.
He described external trauma to the children's bodies as ``minor''
but would not elaborate.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators are awaiting autopsies by the Tarrant County
Medical Examiner to determine the cause of death.
</P>
<P>
   Richards added they are following up several leads and have been
swamped with calls from across the state.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, 74 missing children in Texas the same ages as the
victims showed up in the Texas Department of Public Safety's
Missing Persons Clearinghouse and are being checked by two Texas
Rangers, according to DPS spokesman Mike Cox.
</P>
<P>
   In the drawings, the children bear a striking resemblance to
each other as if they were brother and sister. Both wore pull-up
Mickey Mouse diapers, the boy's blue and the girl's pink. They were
dressed in toddler-size clothing.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators estimate the boy was between 1 and 3 years old,
while the girl is thought to have been between 2 and 4.
</P>
<P>
   The little girl, known simply as ``Victim 2,'' was clad in denim
overalls embroidered with hearts and flowers. A green four-leaf
clover dangled from a chain attached to one of the pockets. The
little boy wore a striped T-shirt, jeans and hiking boots.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have received a lot of calls from law enforcement agencies,
people that have children missing thinking maybe these are their
children,'' Richards said.
</P>
<P>
   Law officers from several counties and towns have joined the
investigation as well as the Texas Department of Public Safety, the
Texas Rangers and support help from the FBI.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, authorities had strung yellow crime scene tape across
the deep incline leading to the shore line of Brushy Creek near
Hutto, population 740.
</P>
<P>
   There, they said, an unidentified couple out for a stroll made
the discovery around 4:30 p.m. Monday and informed local
authorities.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities said they believe the bodies had been in 6 inches of
water near a debris-strewn ravine only a matter of hours.
</P>
<ANNOTATION>
   (STORY CAN END HERE)
</ANNOTATION>
<P>
   ``I've heard it's a pretty popular place to fish,'' said Mike
Gleason, a patrol supervisor for the Sheriff's Department, as he
worked on a crew looking for clues Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ``The sun fades everything our here real fast, so you can pretty
much determine what's old and what's not,'' he added.
</P>
<P>
   By midafternoon, the officers discovered an object a news
photographer said looked like a blood-stained piece of paper. They
carefully lifted it into a paper sack wearing protective gloves but
would not confirm what the object was.
</P>
<P>
   Police also said they are doubtful that the dead female child is
that of Cristy Ryno, a 3-year-old from Irving reported missing on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   XXXXX END OF STORY
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
