struggled to handle the unpredictable flow of ethnic Albanians
fleeing Kosovo. (James Hill/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) UNDATED -- April 20, 1999 -- KITCHEN-WARES, 4-20 --
Various renditions of the ancient mortar and pestle. This simple
tool - a heavy hollowed base with a clublike pounder - looks
hopelessly tedious to use. But in practice they are not only
efficient but effective in ways that no fancy food processor could
ever be. (David Corio/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT6) NEW YORK -- April 20, 1999 -- NY-KUNZ-LANDMARK, 4-20 --
Ray Kunz, the four-star chef without a portfolio, has generated
nearly as much talk about his search for a space for his own
restaurant as he did while cooking at Lespinasse. Finally, he is
hoping to open in Lever House, the landmarked office building high
above Park Avenue seen in this 1996 photo. (Fred Conrad/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) WASHINGTON -- April 20, 1999 -- KOSOVO-U.S., 4-20 --
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright confers with National
