<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, APRIL 21
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-ISRAEL-POLITICS-NYT (moved on Monday, Apr. 19)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Apr. 19,
about the relationship between Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of
Israel and Ehud Barak, a challenger in the election on May 17,
misstated the year in which Mr. Barak led the storming of a Sabena
jet hijacked by terrorists in Tel Aviv. It was 1972, not 1976. A
picture caption misidentified the operation in which Mr. Netanyahu
served under Mr. Barak. It was the storming of the jet, not the
1976 Israeli raid to rescue hostages in Entebbe, Uganda.
</P>
<P>
   BC-E.T.-HUNTER-NYT (moved on Monday, Apr. 19)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Apr. 19,
about William Welch, the first professor to hold an academic chair
devoted to searching for intelligent life beyond Earth, misstated
the affiliation of Dr. Frank Drake, a pioneer in the field. He is a
professor of astronomy at the University of California at Santa
Cruz, not Santa Clara.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-SINGH-NYT (moved on Monday, Apr. 19)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Raghubir Singh sent by the New York Times News
Service on Monday, Apr. 19, misstated his age. He was 56, not 58.
</P>
</TEXT>
