<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CLINTON-VISIT-AUSTIN-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    President cancels Texas trip
 &HT;    By Leah Quin
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ President Bill Clinton called off his trip to
Austin on Tuesday night, saying today's scheduled celebration of
the city's new airport and a fund-raising lunch would be
inappropriate so soon after the school shooting in Colorado.
</P>
<P>
   ``As tomorrow was supposed to be a trip to celebrate the opening
of an airport and to fund-raise, given the tragic circumstances in
Colorado, the president thought it was best not to go,'' said
Elizabeth Newman, assistant press secretary for the White House.
</P>
<P>
   Newman said she did not know if the trip would be rescheduled.
</P>
<P>
   Mayor Kirk Watson, who is in Washington and was scheduled to
return to Austin on Air Force One this morning, said U.S.
Transportation Secretary Rodney Slater was prepared to come in
Clinton's place, but the city decided to cancel the whole event.
</P>
<P>
   ``Instead of us celebrating we're going to pause and say our
prayers for the people in Jefferson County, Colo.,'' Watson said.
He said he called Patricia Holloway, the chair of the Jefferson
County commission, to offer his condolences for the tragedy.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is a disappointment for a lot of people,'' he said of
Clinton's cancellation, ``but in comparison _ there is no
comparison.''
</P>
<P>
   The president had no plans to visit Colorado on Wednesday,
Newman said.
</P>
<P>
   The cancellation upset weeks of planning, forcing city officials
to call off a ceremony at Austin-Bergstrom International Airport
and the Democratic National Committee to nix a fund-raiser at Roy
Spence's home that was expected to raise $350,000.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think everyone attending will agree the president needs to
take care of the country's business first before we have a party,''
Mauro said.
</P>
<P>
   Leah Quin writes for the Austin American-Statesman, Austin,
Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
